sentences: Yank Rachell (born James A. Rachel; March 16, 1903 or 1910 – April 9, 1997) was an American country blues musician who has been called an "elder statesman of the blues".
His career as a performer spanned nearly seventy years, from the late 1920s to the 1990s.
